{
  "texts": [
    "To this end, we utilize an iterated dilated convolutional network [50] to encode the embedding representation of input sentences, which is defined ash t ¼ f W c È k¼0 n=2 e tAEkδ þ b(10)where the dilated window skips over δ inputs at a time, n is the width of the convolutional sliding window, W c is the convolutional kernel, f Á ð Þ is the activation function, È is the vector concatenation, δ is the dilation width, and b is the bias.",
    "When δ > 1, the dilated convolution incorporates a broader context into the representation of a token than the conventional convolution.",
    "Thus, the size of the receptive field increases exponentially with the number of dilated convolution layers, and the contextual information from the entire sequence for the NER task can be captured with a limited number of dilated convolution layers.In NLP tasks, the words in a sentence are generally assumed to obey the Markov assumption.",
    "That is, the probability of the n-th word is based on the n À 1 previous words in the sentence.",
    "However, traditional CNN models do not satisfy the Markov assumption."
  ]
}